arch:property.oc:show_val: A small amount of bone in which there was a fair quantity of digested fragments. Moderate fragmentation, and there tend to be scattered bits, not articulatable elements. Almost no burning. A wide range of degrees of weathering, from quite light to very severe. A mix of animal sizes and taxa. Diagnostics include a couple of sheep/goat forelimb and hindlimb parts, 007-size mandible, cranium, and a metapodial. Sample 1 4 mm flotation sorted 100% and recorded completely. it is a moderate-size sample, consisting mostly of small fragments with a fair amount of skull. Some burning, both high and low temperature, fair amount of digestion. A few fish bones. Many of the smaller fragments are worn as if by water or more likely by trample. Last number: F98.

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
